        • [ - ] Castle - member since 08-Sep-15

          Against Romania Dechamps switched to 4-2-3-1 by bringing Martial to left so Payet could roam free and Coman to right to get crosses to the box. That seemed to work, at least they scored a winning goal which was due to Payet's more free role. So France continued with the same line up they finished with Romania but this time it didn't work, particularly Martial was awful and Payet dropped too deep to get the ball which meant he wasn't enough in scoring positions. Changing back to 4-3-3 and bringing Griezmann got them victory but they are still to actually impress in this tournament. Two last minute wins is quite exciting but I'm sure they want to win this match earlier this time. Switzerland is their toughest opposition so far, now it's time to put all the pieces together. It might be too late for that in final stages.
